\h ACRONYMS \d

During your adventures, you may encounter various acronyms. Here is a guide to what they mean.
Note that the use of acronyms in IC communication is prohibited! (What's "IC"? See below!)

AFK     Away From Keyboard`

BRB     Be Right Back`

IC      In Character`
        Something said or done in the context of role-playing.

INPC    Interactive Non-Player Character`
        A character that is usually controlled by the server, and sometimes controlled, or otherwise managed, by staff.

IRL     In Real Life`

MUD     Multi-User Dungeon`
        This generally refers to a virtual world in its totality.

NPC     Non-Player Character`
        A character controlled by the server.

OOC     Out Of Character`
        Something said or done as a player, outside the context of role-playing.

PC      Player Character`
        A character controlled by a human player.

PD      Permadeath`
        When a PC dies, it is truly dead; a deceased PC cannot return to the virtual world in any way, shape, or form.

PKing   Player Killing`
        When one PC kills another PC.

PvP     Player vs. Player`
        The act of one PC attacking another PC.

RP      Role-Playing`

